The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 18 March is 41,027 (4,748.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 13 March, there were 293 new confirmed cases (33.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 06 March, there were 304 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 4% (11 fewer cases).
